						<summary>

						<p>Back of a wall set up outside the west wall of the Sōmanatha temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 13th century.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record refers to some gift of land and other money-incomes by some <hi rend="italic">seṭṭis.</hi> It is dated the cyclic year Pārthiva, in the 13th day of the summer season, Saṁkrānti, the details being insufficient for verification.</p>						

